1
00:01:30,800 --> 00:01:34,520
=Lady Liberty=

2
00:01:35,020 --> 00:01:37,940
=Episode 2=

3
00:01:50,940 --> 00:01:51,500
Hello, Mei.

4
00:01:51,940 --> 00:01:52,700
I'll be home later.

5
00:01:52,777 --> 00:01:54,140
I need to take care of something.

6
00:01:54,200 --> 00:01:55,533
Don't wait for me for dinner.

7
00:01:55,540 --> 00:01:56,060
Okay, bye.

8
00:01:59,620 --> 00:02:00,060
Li Weifeng.

9
00:02:06,780 --> 00:02:09,900
(Shattered Six States update)

10
00:02:19,380 --> 00:02:20,940
(Chapter 285,
The Sea of Glass, latest update)

11
00:02:20,940 --> 00:02:22,622
(Chapter 284,
Vessel of Immortality, latest update)

12
00:02:28,620 --> 00:02:30,460
(Shattered Six States
Chapter 285, The Sea of Glass)

13
00:02:30,460 --> 00:02:32,100
So, you mean shared memories?

14
00:02:33,711 --> 00:02:35,330
(Year 2023)
Like the male and female leads

15
00:02:35,355 --> 00:02:36,133
having twin souls?

16
00:02:37,533 --> 00:02:39,380
I think the male lead
discovered it first,

17
00:02:39,460 --> 00:02:40,822
but he didn't tell the female lead.

18
00:02:40,888 --> 00:02:42,380
She only found out later on her own.

19
00:02:44,460 --> 00:02:46,444
But even if she finds out,
she might not agree.

20
00:02:47,900 --> 00:02:48,820
If it were me,

21
00:02:49,180 --> 00:02:50,500
I wouldn't want

22
00:02:50,622 --> 00:02:52,740
to share something
like soul memories with anyone.

23
00:02:55,020 --> 00:02:56,340
She might agree in the end,

24
00:02:56,540 --> 00:02:57,420
but it would

25
00:02:58,340 --> 00:03:00,020
be a painful process.

26
00:03:04,900 --> 00:03:06,900
At least the pain gets shared.

27
00:03:07,620 --> 00:03:08,580
Pain can't be shared,

28
00:03:09,940 --> 00:03:11,420
but at least someone can understand

29
00:03:11,980 --> 00:03:12,860
that your pain

30
00:03:13,180 --> 00:03:14,540
is truly felt by someone else.

31
00:03:21,220 --> 00:03:21,780
Come on.

32
00:03:21,780 --> 00:03:22,490
What are you doing?

33
00:03:22,500 --> 00:03:23,780
Let's go.

34
00:03:23,780 --> 00:03:24,660
Put me down.

35
00:03:35,540 --> 00:03:36,460
That was so well said.

36
00:03:37,260 --> 00:03:38,220
I have to write it down.

37
00:03:40,900 --> 00:03:41,780
Are you childish?

38
00:03:42,540 --> 00:03:43,300
You're right.

39
00:03:43,500 --> 00:03:44,420
Why write it down now?

40
00:03:44,420 --> 00:03:45,140
Write it tomorrow.

41
00:03:45,140 --> 00:03:45,700
Feel it first.

42
00:03:45,700 --> 00:03:46,700
Don't come over.

43
00:03:46,700 --> 00:03:47,866
- Don't come over.
- Too late. Feel it.

44
00:03:47,940 --> 00:03:48,700
I'm in pain.

45
00:03:48,700 --> 00:03:49,660
You feel it with me.

46
00:04:04,755 --> 00:04:06,620
I didn't expect
your wife to be like this.

47
00:04:08,500 --> 00:04:09,940
I know she's an educated person.

48
00:04:11,333 --> 00:04:12,580
The reason I ignored you before

49
00:04:12,711 --> 00:04:14,711
was that I didn't want
to hurt an innocent person.

50
00:04:15,980 --> 00:04:18,888
But when I met her, I didn't expect her
to speak to me like that.

51
00:04:20,740 --> 00:04:22,060
Your life must not be easy.

52
00:04:22,140 --> 00:04:23,300
I can divorce her,

53
00:04:24,422 --> 00:04:25,460
and leave with nothing.

54
00:04:28,700 --> 00:04:29,420
If you...

55
00:04:34,500 --> 00:04:35,580
I can do anything.

56
00:04:41,100 --> 00:04:42,820
You worked so hard to earn the money.

57
00:04:43,422 --> 00:04:45,755
Walking away with
nothing would be such a waste.

58
00:04:48,140 --> 00:04:48,660
Of course,

59
00:04:50,060 --> 00:04:51,380
I can earn my own money too.

60
00:04:52,020 --> 00:04:53,020
I'm not after your money.

61
00:04:54,700 --> 00:04:55,540
But if your marriage

62
00:04:55,540 --> 00:04:56,900
is really that difficult,

63
00:04:58,460 --> 00:05:00,020
you should still make preparations

64
00:05:00,222 --> 00:05:02,066
for the transfer and division of assets.

65
00:05:02,820 --> 00:05:04,060
You make a good point.

66
00:05:05,060 --> 00:05:06,300
I haven't thought that far yet.

67
00:05:08,900 --> 00:05:09,900
I know a lawyer.

68
00:05:10,777 --> 00:05:12,733
I can recommend one
to you when the time comes.

69
00:05:12,755 --> 00:05:13,933
You can get a consultation.

70
00:05:14,380 --> 00:05:15,511
Better to be prepared.

71
00:05:16,288 --> 00:05:17,133
What do you think?

72
00:05:18,100 --> 00:05:18,460
Okay.

73
00:05:23,300 --> 00:05:24,660
I kind of don't know what to say.

74
00:05:25,377 --> 00:05:26,933
Just keep the right mindset.

75
00:05:28,444 --> 00:05:29,644
Keep the right mindset.

76
00:05:32,022 --> 00:05:32,800
Let's go.

77
00:05:42,660 --> 00:05:43,266
It's a mess.

78
00:05:43,980 --> 00:05:44,300
Alright.

79
00:05:45,140 --> 00:05:45,900
I'm a bit nervous.

80
00:05:46,180 --> 00:05:46,900
Don't be nervous.

81
00:05:57,260 --> 00:05:57,620
This way.

82
00:06:29,140 --> 00:06:29,940
Mr. He Han.

83
00:06:46,060 --> 00:06:46,780
Mr. He Han.

84
00:06:47,100 --> 00:06:48,140
Just call me Lily.

85
00:06:48,500 --> 00:06:49,500
I'm 23 this year.

86
00:06:50,580 --> 00:06:51,580
Chen Zheng, 24.

87
00:06:51,666 --> 00:06:52,733
Hello, Mr. He Han.

88
00:06:58,220 --> 00:06:59,740
What do you usually read?

89
00:07:00,940 --> 00:07:01,500
I'll go first.

90
00:07:02,820 --> 00:07:05,140
I like One Hundred Years of Solitude,

91
00:07:06,311 --> 00:07:07,380
Temple of Earth and I,

92
00:07:07,780 --> 00:07:09,620
and I also quite like The Little Prince.

93
00:07:12,180 --> 00:07:14,460
Your range is quite wide, huh?

94
00:07:14,940 --> 00:07:15,460
Oh?

95
00:07:23,933 --> 00:07:24,911
What about you?

96
00:07:25,860 --> 00:07:27,540
I prefer short stories.

97
00:07:28,060 --> 00:07:29,380
Short stories are interesting.

98
00:07:29,620 --> 00:07:30,380
What do you read?

99
00:07:30,940 --> 00:07:32,100
My favorite

100
00:07:32,244 --> 00:07:33,600
is The Old Man and the Sea.

101
00:07:37,340 --> 00:07:37,900
You two,

102
00:07:38,260 --> 00:07:39,220
I'm really sorry,

103
00:07:39,420 --> 00:07:41,140
but please go back and tell Mr. Fan

104
00:07:41,780 --> 00:07:42,660
we're not a good fit.

105
00:07:42,660 --> 00:07:44,490
Your tastes are too highbrow.

106
00:07:44,490 --> 00:07:45,860
I'm just an online fiction author.

107
00:07:46,140 --> 00:07:47,155
I can't handle something

108
00:07:47,160 --> 00:07:49,022
on the level
of One Hundred Years of Solitude.

109
00:07:52,340 --> 00:07:53,060
Thank you.

110
00:07:57,380 --> 00:07:58,180
What a coincidence.

111
00:07:58,620 --> 00:07:59,500
Let me introduce you.

112
00:07:59,500 --> 00:08:01,133
This is my former editor, Lin Zhanqiao.

113
00:08:01,140 --> 00:08:01,780
She's great.

114
00:08:01,822 --> 00:08:03,700
She never talks about things like
One Hundred Years of Solitude

115
00:08:03,700 --> 00:08:04,733
or The Old Man and the Sea.

116
00:08:04,755 --> 00:08:06,780
She only cares about
whether there's space in my room

117
00:08:06,780 --> 00:08:08,688
for her toothbrush,
slippers, and pillow.

118
00:08:09,911 --> 00:08:11,200
Why don't you come on in?

119
00:08:48,620 --> 00:08:49,380
Hey, Zhao Lanxin.

120
00:08:50,460 --> 00:08:52,340
If Shattered Six States
is sold to Mr. Fan,

121
00:08:52,460 --> 00:08:53,340
how much can he offer?

122
00:08:54,140 --> 00:08:55,020
How much do I get?

123
00:08:58,980 --> 00:08:59,740
Alright, got it.

124
00:09:10,100 --> 00:09:10,700
Hello, Mr. Fan.

125
00:09:11,420 --> 00:09:12,100
If you want

126
00:09:13,420 --> 00:09:14,380
Shattered Six States,

127
00:09:14,940 --> 00:09:16,540
add another five million to your offer.

128
00:09:17,140 --> 00:09:18,620
If you agree, we have a deal.

129
00:09:23,740 --> 00:09:24,888
You can think about it.

130
00:09:27,740 --> 00:09:28,100
Bye.

131
00:09:32,460 --> 00:09:33,100
Congratulations

132
00:09:34,460 --> 00:09:35,500
in every way.

133
00:09:40,140 --> 00:09:42,340
The three words that waste
the most feelings and effort

134
00:09:42,980 --> 00:09:43,820
are "can't let go."

135
00:10:07,940 --> 00:10:08,300
Hello?

136
00:10:08,320 --> 00:10:09,500
Lin Zhanqiao, you wouldn't really...

137
00:10:09,500 --> 00:10:11,260
That's right. I called Mr. Fan.

138
00:10:11,460 --> 00:10:12,060
I agreed.

139
00:10:14,022 --> 00:10:15,177
Five million more.

140
00:10:16,466 --> 00:10:18,540
Everything I've done for
the company over the years

141
00:10:18,660 --> 00:10:20,220
is worth earning
that extra five million.

142
00:10:21,155 --> 00:10:23,000
And of course, you should thank me.

143
00:10:23,660 --> 00:10:24,660
No matter where it's said,

144
00:10:25,140 --> 00:10:26,780
I just raised
your value by five million.

145
00:10:57,400 --> 00:10:58,777
(From childhood to now,)

146
00:10:59,740 --> 00:11:01,220
(we learned in the classroom)

147
00:11:02,100 --> 00:11:03,460
(how to make new friends,)

148
00:11:04,500 --> 00:11:05,700
(how to welcome a new life,)

149
00:11:06,533 --> 00:11:08,133
(and how to gain new knowledge.)

150
00:11:10,300 --> 00:11:10,820
(And now,)

151
00:11:12,260 --> 00:11:15,300
(life has used a long farewell)

152
00:11:16,660 --> 00:11:18,780
(to teach me how
to let go of old attachments.)

153
00:11:26,380 --> 00:11:27,380
♪Never Stop♪

154
00:11:27,780 --> 00:11:28,740
♪Never Stop♪

155
00:11:28,740 --> 00:11:32,220
(Shattered Six States)

156
00:11:32,220 --> 00:11:32,860
♪Never Stop♪

157
00:11:32,860 --> 00:11:33,980
♪Watch my words come alive in bloom♪

158
00:11:33,980 --> 00:11:35,570
♪Unleash six states in a chain of blows♪

159
00:11:35,580 --> 00:11:36,780
♪See a genius born to soar♪

160
00:11:36,780 --> 00:11:38,280
♪Rising high where the wide skies glow♪

161
00:11:38,340 --> 00:11:39,540
♪If you can catch my shadow♪

162
00:11:39,540 --> 00:11:40,940
♪You can cross the world and roam free♪

163
00:11:40,940 --> 00:11:42,540
(Dingqi Reading secures exclusive
rights to Shattered Six States)

164
00:11:42,540 --> 00:11:44,020
(Editor's Office)

165
00:11:44,700 --> 00:11:46,100
♪Lighting up every hidden place♪

166
00:11:46,340 --> 00:11:47,820
♪I once climbed rooftops all alone♪

167
00:11:47,820 --> 00:11:48,860
♪Searching for the stars above♪

168
00:11:48,860 --> 00:11:50,300
♪Until I saw your eyes aglow♪

169
00:11:50,420 --> 00:11:51,420
♪Shining through the city lights♪

170
00:11:51,460 --> 00:11:52,666
(Responsible editor, Lin Zhanqiao)

171
00:11:52,820 --> 00:11:54,180
♪The legend I had chased all along♪

172
00:11:54,180 --> 00:11:57,620
♪Never Stop♪

173
00:12:16,860 --> 00:12:17,540
Having noodles?

174
00:12:24,100 --> 00:12:24,460
Look.

175
00:12:24,820 --> 00:12:25,622
This is for you.

176
00:12:26,380 --> 00:12:27,540
We're family now,

177
00:12:27,666 --> 00:12:29,244
so no need to be polite with me.

178
00:12:30,060 --> 00:12:31,260
I've kept this for many years.

179
00:12:31,333 --> 00:12:32,955
I couldn't even
bring myself to drink it.

180
00:12:33,820 --> 00:12:34,380
Take it.

181
00:12:35,260 --> 00:12:37,180
When Shattered Six States is finished,

182
00:12:37,540 --> 00:12:38,860
open it and celebrate properly.

183
00:12:39,177 --> 00:12:40,422
What would you like to eat?

184
00:12:40,460 --> 00:12:41,140
I'll pass.

185
00:12:42,300 --> 00:12:43,200
Just a glass of water.

186
00:12:44,422 --> 00:12:45,580
I've been talking all day,

187
00:12:45,740 --> 00:12:46,500
and I'm parched.

188
00:12:49,420 --> 00:12:51,500
As soon as news of
our partnership went public,

189
00:12:51,740 --> 00:12:53,340
it's been non-stop interviews

190
00:12:54,220 --> 00:12:56,180
and people lining up

191
00:12:56,340 --> 00:12:57,955
to negotiate film and TV rights.

192
00:12:59,500 --> 00:13:00,060
How about you?

193
00:13:00,740 --> 00:13:02,140
Have you found your editor?

194
00:13:02,540 --> 00:13:03,020
Yes.

195
00:13:03,620 --> 00:13:04,180
Already?

196
00:13:04,820 --> 00:13:05,820
What kind of person

197
00:13:05,820 --> 00:13:06,940
would meet your standards?

198
00:13:08,620 --> 00:13:09,220
Do I know them?

199
00:13:09,780 --> 00:13:10,180
You do.

200
00:13:10,511 --> 00:13:10,980
Who is it?

201
00:13:11,355 --> 00:13:12,533
You'll see in a moment.

202
00:13:16,340 --> 00:13:16,940
Fan.

203
00:13:17,460 --> 00:13:18,020
He Han.

204
00:13:23,820 --> 00:13:24,780
Why are you back?

205
00:13:25,780 --> 00:13:27,020
Weren't you in Singapore?

206
00:13:27,222 --> 00:13:29,355
I'm not staying there anymore.
I came back yesterday.

207
00:13:31,700 --> 00:13:33,530
You came back with your husband?

208
00:13:33,530 --> 00:13:35,260
He didn't come back. I came back alone.

209
00:13:35,940 --> 00:13:36,420
Divorced.

210
00:13:38,620 --> 00:13:39,540
Again?

211
00:13:39,820 --> 00:13:40,660
So is that illegal?

212
00:13:44,060 --> 00:13:44,540
It's her?

213
00:13:45,600 --> 00:13:47,155
I was the one who looked for him.

214
00:13:47,533 --> 00:13:49,177
Didn't you just get back yesterday?

215
00:13:49,266 --> 00:13:49,822
Yes.

216
00:13:50,044 --> 00:13:51,260
As soon as I got back, I heard

217
00:13:51,260 --> 00:13:53,533
the big news about
Shattered Six States changing hands.

218
00:13:53,900 --> 00:13:55,580
So I called He Han.

219
00:13:55,860 --> 00:13:57,580
He needs an editor, and I need a job.

220
00:13:57,755 --> 00:13:58,933
It worked out perfectly.

221
00:14:01,340 --> 00:14:02,940
How could you hire her?

222
00:14:03,511 --> 00:14:04,860
How did you even agree on this?

223
00:14:04,860 --> 00:14:06,200
How much are you paying her?

224
00:14:07,220 --> 00:14:08,700
Let me tell you,

225
00:14:09,140 --> 00:14:10,700
this woman only cares about money.

226
00:14:11,300 --> 00:14:12,580
I've seen it first-hand.

227
00:14:12,860 --> 00:14:14,370
Don't say I didn't warn you.

228
00:14:14,370 --> 00:14:15,180
Watch what you say.

229
00:14:20,060 --> 00:14:22,380
Ms. Lin, guess who
He Han picked as his editor?

230
00:14:22,460 --> 00:14:23,444
Not interested.

231
00:14:23,740 --> 00:14:24,580
Just guess the age.

232
00:14:24,800 --> 00:14:25,800
I'm talking about age.

233
00:14:26,100 --> 00:14:27,140
Start training her at 18,

234
00:14:27,140 --> 00:14:28,170
and ten years later she will be 28.

235
00:14:28,170 --> 00:14:30,111
- That's one way to go about it.
- Forty-six.

236
00:14:32,580 --> 00:14:33,100
Who is it?

237
00:14:34,020 --> 00:14:34,460
Dai Shan.

238
00:14:35,660 --> 00:14:36,580
Mr. Fan's ex-wife?

239
00:14:37,820 --> 00:14:38,260
Wasn't she

240
00:14:39,060 --> 00:14:40,700
with some businessman in Singapore?

241
00:14:40,860 --> 00:14:41,500
Divorced.

242
00:14:41,900 --> 00:14:43,660
She's back to her old line of work.

243
00:14:46,222 --> 00:14:47,155
It costs a bit more,

244
00:14:47,422 --> 00:14:48,355
but she's not bad.

245
00:15:02,200 --> 00:15:03,200
Hello, Mr. Ling.

246
00:15:10,488 --> 00:15:12,177
What is it that had
to be discussed outside?

247
00:15:12,660 --> 00:15:14,020
When will Mr. Fan's money arrive?

248
00:15:14,220 --> 00:15:15,020
Within a week.

249
00:15:20,311 --> 00:15:21,860
The company was founded by three of us.

250
00:15:22,660 --> 00:15:24,380
Back then,
we gave Zhanqiao an equal share

251
00:15:24,780 --> 00:15:25,940
because she had He Han.

252
00:15:26,444 --> 00:15:27,466
Now that it's sold,

253
00:15:27,511 --> 00:15:28,780
she's not that important anymore.

254
00:15:29,088 --> 00:15:30,022
What do you think?

255
00:15:30,155 --> 00:15:31,311
What do you want to do?

256
00:15:31,620 --> 00:15:32,740
Reduce her shareholding.

257
00:15:37,260 --> 00:15:37,940
On what grounds?

258
00:15:40,220 --> 00:15:41,140
That's your job.

259
00:15:53,860 --> 00:15:55,860
(Half A Month Later)

260
00:16:00,820 --> 00:16:01,860
(Shattered Six States
real-time popularity)

261
00:16:01,860 --> 00:16:02,940
(Bestseller List Daily Rank 01)

262
00:16:02,940 --> 00:16:03,980
(Global Ranking 01)

263
00:16:03,980 --> 00:16:06,420
(Dingqi Reading Platform,
Daily Rank, Shattered Six States)

264
00:16:06,420 --> 00:16:07,180
Qingshan Moran.

265
00:16:07,577 --> 00:16:08,266
Over here.

266
00:16:09,860 --> 00:16:10,580
Fluorescent Light.

267
00:16:13,100 --> 00:16:13,940
Flowers Ate Zhuge.

268
00:16:14,220 --> 00:16:14,620
Here.

269
00:16:16,340 --> 00:16:16,980
Old Hand.

270
00:16:19,740 --> 00:16:20,500
Mosquito Water Ice.

271
00:16:23,700 --> 00:16:24,580
One Penny Gentleman.

272
00:16:27,777 --> 00:16:29,100
First of all, congratulations.

273
00:16:29,180 --> 00:16:30,980
You've stood out among 170 people

274
00:16:31,111 --> 00:16:32,688
and now have the chance to become

275
00:16:32,755 --> 00:16:34,420
a new author working with Chenxing.

276
00:16:39,020 --> 00:16:40,220
What does that mean?

277
00:16:40,500 --> 00:16:41,180
Nothing much.

278
00:16:41,980 --> 00:16:42,540
Does it work?

279
00:16:43,260 --> 00:16:44,066
Hard to say.

280
00:16:45,780 --> 00:16:47,060
What I'm about to send you

281
00:16:47,600 --> 00:16:49,600
is the project brief
we'll be working on.

282
00:16:51,500 --> 00:16:53,222
The story concept
belongs to the company,

283
00:16:53,230 --> 00:16:55,470
and it's already been
officially registered and protected.

284
00:16:56,140 --> 00:16:58,355
One author will be
selected from the six of you.

285
00:16:58,980 --> 00:17:00,060
The sections marked in red

286
00:17:00,220 --> 00:17:02,260
are what you need to take home, write,

287
00:17:02,500 --> 00:17:03,540
and submit back to me.

288
00:17:03,980 --> 00:17:05,622
Each of you has a different part.

289
00:17:06,100 --> 00:17:06,900
Three days.

290
00:17:07,266 --> 00:17:08,844
I need at least 50,000 words.

291
00:17:09,466 --> 00:17:11,010
Fifty thousand?

292
00:17:11,010 --> 00:17:11,900
In three days?

293
00:17:12,220 --> 00:17:13,288
You heard that right.

294
00:17:13,377 --> 00:17:14,380
Fifty thousand words.

295
00:17:14,533 --> 00:17:16,160
Writing online fiction is physical work.

296
00:17:16,420 --> 00:17:17,380
Under any circumstances,

297
00:17:17,500 --> 00:17:19,780
you must maintain
both output and quality.

298
00:17:20,133 --> 00:17:21,650
If you can't write 10,000 words a day,

299
00:17:21,650 --> 00:17:23,340
you won't even make it through my door.

300
00:17:24,460 --> 00:17:25,540
If it's padded writing,

301
00:17:25,940 --> 00:17:26,980
I'll still show you out.

302
00:17:28,140 --> 00:17:29,700
Since you've chosen this line of work,

303
00:17:29,820 --> 00:17:31,540
you'll be evaluated every single day.

304
00:17:31,700 --> 00:17:33,600
Out of more than 20 million
online fiction authors,

305
00:17:33,688 --> 00:17:36,288
you have to break into the top 20
just to be seen and remembered.

306
00:17:38,420 --> 00:17:40,020
One out of six will be chosen.

307
00:17:40,780 --> 00:17:41,340
Which means

308
00:17:41,340 --> 00:17:43,220
everyone sitting across from you
and beside you

309
00:17:43,220 --> 00:17:44,180
is your competition.

310
00:17:45,420 --> 00:17:46,060
In a moment,

311
00:17:46,060 --> 00:17:47,740
I will introduce your assigned editors.

312
00:17:49,300 --> 00:17:50,100
Fragile.

313
00:17:50,620 --> 00:17:51,100
Mantou.

314
00:17:51,260 --> 00:17:51,820
Naobaijin.

315
00:17:52,420 --> 00:17:54,933
You can choose for yourselves
who you want to work with.

316
00:17:55,888 --> 00:17:56,780
I have a question.

317
00:17:57,180 --> 00:17:59,066
This project we're
benchmarking against...

318
00:17:59,340 --> 00:18:01,980
What genre and tier does it fall under?

319
00:18:02,180 --> 00:18:03,020
Fantasy cultivation.

320
00:18:03,700 --> 00:18:04,340
A top-tier work.

321
00:18:04,844 --> 00:18:06,466
Something like Shattered Six States.

322
00:18:06,900 --> 00:18:08,020
It's already a massive hit.

323
00:18:08,100 --> 00:18:09,020
I don't want imitation.

324
00:18:10,500 --> 00:18:12,260
I want your own voice.

325
00:18:32,444 --> 00:18:33,300
This author is the one

326
00:18:33,420 --> 00:18:35,300
who previously
wrote The Desert Rises to Fame.

327
00:18:35,700 --> 00:18:36,460
How old is he?

328
00:18:37,020 --> 00:18:38,340
How old...

329
00:18:38,500 --> 00:18:39,020
No idea.

330
00:18:39,380 --> 00:18:40,140
Is there a photo?

331
00:18:40,420 --> 00:18:40,980
Let me check.

332
00:18:41,900 --> 00:18:42,780
A photo...

333
00:18:46,820 --> 00:18:48,140
Miss, could I borrow the vinegar?

334
00:18:51,980 --> 00:18:52,780
Found it.

335
00:18:53,780 --> 00:18:54,490
So handsome.

336
00:18:54,490 --> 00:18:54,860
Right?

337
00:18:54,860 --> 00:18:55,620
Is he married?

338
00:18:55,820 --> 00:18:56,420
No idea.

339
00:18:56,500 --> 00:18:57,540
He's really handsome.

340
00:19:01,222 --> 00:19:03,177
He looks like the one
who just borrowed the vinegar.

341
00:19:06,340 --> 00:19:07,100
Mr. He Han,

342
00:19:07,220 --> 00:19:08,420
can I take a photo with you?

343
00:19:08,700 --> 00:19:09,460
Of course. Come on.

344
00:19:11,100 --> 00:19:11,700
Thank you.

345
00:19:14,820 --> 00:19:15,660
It's a rare chance.

346
00:19:15,660 --> 00:19:16,780
Let's take one together.

347
00:19:16,780 --> 00:19:17,600
- Sure. Really?
- Alright?

348
00:19:17,620 --> 00:19:18,260
One, two, three.

349
00:19:22,700 --> 00:19:24,940
(Dingqi Reading Platform)

350
00:19:24,940 --> 00:19:28,140
(Shattered Six States Promotion Event)

351
00:19:36,180 --> 00:19:36,660
How is it?

352
00:19:37,540 --> 00:19:38,380
You can see

353
00:19:39,100 --> 00:19:40,580
our sincerity, right?

354
00:19:41,780 --> 00:19:43,420
Just have him show his face.

355
00:19:44,088 --> 00:19:46,060
Consider it doing
our platform a favor, alright?

356
00:19:46,260 --> 00:19:47,620
He agreed to a video call.

357
00:19:48,180 --> 00:19:49,540
Just a video call?

358
00:19:52,580 --> 00:19:54,380
There's also an interview later.

359
00:19:54,540 --> 00:19:55,540
Have him talk about

360
00:19:55,860 --> 00:19:58,060
his contract termination
with Chenxing and Lin Zhanqiao.

361
00:19:58,177 --> 00:19:59,220
That's a private matter.

362
00:19:59,755 --> 00:20:01,140
It's not convenient for him to answer.

363
00:20:01,140 --> 00:20:02,420
Next, we'll switch the camera to

364
00:20:02,420 --> 00:20:04,260
Mr. He Han,
the author of Shattered Six States.

365
00:20:04,311 --> 00:20:05,940
(Shattered Six States Special Promotion)
Thank you to everyone here.

366
00:20:06,380 --> 00:20:08,540
Thank you for
supporting Shattered Six States.

367
00:20:09,420 --> 00:20:10,100
Mr. He Han,

368
00:20:10,100 --> 00:20:11,540
you're as distinctive as ever.

369
00:20:11,540 --> 00:20:13,100
With the success
of Shattered Six States,

370
00:20:13,100 --> 00:20:15,100
do you have any secrets
to share with everyone?

371
00:20:16,500 --> 00:20:17,340
Love life.

372
00:20:17,980 --> 00:20:18,660
Sleep more.

373
00:20:19,340 --> 00:20:20,380
Eat hot food.

374
00:20:20,460 --> 00:20:22,100
I heard your event serves cold dishes,

375
00:20:22,100 --> 00:20:22,860
so I didn't go.

376
00:20:23,780 --> 00:20:24,260
Also,

377
00:20:24,940 --> 00:20:26,580
learn to appreciate beautiful things,

378
00:20:26,688 --> 00:20:27,900
especially beautiful women.

379
00:20:28,580 --> 00:20:30,780
Mr. He Han, you're so humorous,
and entertaining.

380
00:20:30,780 --> 00:20:31,900
I'm serious.

381
00:20:32,060 --> 00:20:34,020
Mr. He Han, have you just had lunch?

382
00:20:34,820 --> 00:20:35,140
Yes.

383
00:20:35,580 --> 00:20:36,860
Brunch.

384
00:20:37,380 --> 00:20:39,460
Will you be joining our
round-table discussion later?

385
00:20:40,620 --> 00:20:41,260
I can't.

386
00:20:41,377 --> 00:20:42,460
I need to go buy a car.

387
00:20:43,660 --> 00:20:44,500
What kind of car?

388
00:20:45,066 --> 00:20:46,140
I made some money, right?

389
00:20:46,244 --> 00:20:47,400
So, it's something expensive.

390
00:20:50,620 --> 00:20:52,380
Sir, this is our top configuration.

391
00:20:52,700 --> 00:20:53,700
If you're interested,

392
00:20:53,700 --> 00:20:55,560
we can arrange
a test drive registration for you.

393
00:20:55,666 --> 00:20:56,900
How long before delivery?

394
00:20:57,577 --> 00:20:59,680
That depends on your configuration
and payment method.

395
00:20:59,820 --> 00:21:01,580
Generally, it takes six to eight weeks.

396
00:21:01,688 --> 00:21:02,480
I'll take this one.

397
00:21:02,540 --> 00:21:03,820
The top configuration.

398
00:21:04,060 --> 00:21:04,844
I want it today.

399
00:21:06,220 --> 00:21:07,890
I'll need to confirm with the manager.

400
00:21:07,890 --> 00:21:08,711
No need to confirm.

401
00:21:08,780 --> 00:21:09,500
Where do I pay?

402
00:21:43,466 --> 00:21:45,760
All the platform's resources
went to Shattered Six States.

403
00:21:45,940 --> 00:21:47,980
The few novels we launched last week

404
00:21:48,500 --> 00:21:49,660
barely made any impact.

405
00:21:50,688 --> 00:21:52,822
Dingqi Reading's funds
have already come in.

406
00:21:53,260 --> 00:21:55,180
Speaking of which,
we should thank Lin Zhanqiao.

407
00:21:55,340 --> 00:21:57,200
She got an extra
five million from Mr. Fan.

408
00:21:57,600 --> 00:21:59,860
I've nearly finalized the company's
new round of financing.

409
00:21:59,900 --> 00:22:01,422
The process will start next month.

410
00:22:08,177 --> 00:22:09,600
So, have you figured it out?

411
00:22:09,822 --> 00:22:11,933
How to persuade her
to reduce her shareholding?

412
00:22:12,133 --> 00:22:14,266
We need to do it
before the funding comes in.

413
00:22:15,420 --> 00:22:15,860
I haven't.

414
00:22:20,620 --> 00:22:21,780
When He Han was here,

415
00:22:21,780 --> 00:22:23,577
every novel she worked on became a hit.

416
00:22:23,780 --> 00:22:24,860
Now that he's gone,

417
00:22:25,420 --> 00:22:27,020
if she can't produce another He Han,

418
00:22:27,500 --> 00:22:28,970
her reputation

419
00:22:28,970 --> 00:22:30,377
as a top promoter and top editor

420
00:22:30,540 --> 00:22:31,733
will have to be given back.

421
00:22:31,820 --> 00:22:33,660
I also heard the platform returned

422
00:22:33,660 --> 00:22:35,780
the film rights for
At the End of Yue Lu Lights

423
00:22:36,100 --> 00:22:38,400
and raised the price
to acquire Shattered Six States.

424
00:22:38,740 --> 00:22:40,780
We're losing on both ends now.

425
00:22:41,288 --> 00:22:43,760
And you're still not considering
having her reduce her shares?

426
00:22:45,060 --> 00:22:46,460
What I'm considering is

427
00:22:46,622 --> 00:22:47,555
having her leave.

428
00:23:09,260 --> 00:23:10,780
But she founded the company.

429
00:23:11,220 --> 00:23:12,940
She can keep the name Chenxing,

430
00:23:13,580 --> 00:23:14,740
but everything else, I take.

431
00:23:25,300 --> 00:23:26,900
You two are classmates. I'm not.

432
00:23:27,000 --> 00:23:29,688
You can choose to stand with your
classmate through thick and thin,

433
00:23:29,770 --> 00:23:31,955
and I can take the new funding
and start something new.

434
00:23:33,311 --> 00:23:34,420
On one side is friendship,

435
00:23:35,266 --> 00:23:36,533
and on the other is the market.

436
00:23:37,340 --> 00:23:39,180
You still have a choice.

437
00:23:46,100 --> 00:23:46,940
Let's call it a day.

438
00:23:47,580 --> 00:23:48,740
Go back and prepare well.

439
00:23:49,220 --> 00:23:49,980
Lin Zhanqiao!

440
00:23:50,022 --> 00:23:50,844
What are you doing?

441
00:23:50,866 --> 00:23:51,980
You're using your authors!

442
00:23:52,220 --> 00:23:53,000
What are you doing?

443
00:23:53,288 --> 00:23:54,533
You'll get what's coming to you!

444
00:24:00,260 --> 00:24:01,060
A new author, right?

445
00:24:02,580 --> 00:24:02,860
Sit.

446
00:24:09,620 --> 00:24:10,140
What is this?

447
00:24:11,420 --> 00:24:13,488
You promised you'd
let me write this novel.

448
00:24:14,244 --> 00:24:15,888
Why did you give it to someone else?

449
00:24:25,444 --> 00:24:27,866
This is the author
of At the End of Yue Lu Lights,

450
00:24:27,911 --> 00:24:28,955
Zhugan Dalan.

451
00:24:29,133 --> 00:24:31,888
He also stood out among several
candidates in a writing trial before.

452
00:24:31,900 --> 00:24:33,660
I'll use him as an example for you.

453
00:24:35,140 --> 00:24:36,380
The performance of

454
00:24:36,466 --> 00:24:39,311
At the End of Yue Lu Lights did not
meet the company's expectations.

455
00:24:39,400 --> 00:24:40,555
So, the company has decided

456
00:24:40,560 --> 00:24:42,333
to terminate collaboration
on his next project.

457
00:24:42,340 --> 00:24:43,755
It was planned for 1,200 chapters.

458
00:24:44,140 --> 00:24:45,460
I've already completed 400,

459
00:24:45,460 --> 00:24:47,222
and there are
still two-thirds unfinished.

460
00:24:47,300 --> 00:24:48,340
How is that not meeting the requirement?

461
00:24:48,340 --> 00:24:50,888
Four hundred chapters published
and still no recognition.

462
00:24:51,140 --> 00:24:51,900
That means

463
00:24:52,740 --> 00:24:54,780
I won't continue
to waste time on this project.

464
00:24:55,740 --> 00:24:56,860
If you want to continue,

465
00:24:57,111 --> 00:24:57,700
that's fine.

466
00:24:57,700 --> 00:24:59,140
I can assign you a different project.

467
00:25:00,940 --> 00:25:02,140
But if you don't,

468
00:25:02,400 --> 00:25:03,955
whether you terminate the contract

469
00:25:03,980 --> 00:25:05,066
or leave it unfinished,

470
00:25:05,300 --> 00:25:06,100
I have no objection.

471
00:25:09,020 --> 00:25:09,820
Lin Zhanqiao,

472
00:25:12,460 --> 00:25:14,660
you can't expect everyone to be He Han.

473
00:25:14,660 --> 00:25:15,777
You're overthinking it.

474
00:25:16,820 --> 00:25:18,700
I only expect
to see you on the front page

475
00:25:18,700 --> 00:25:19,530
of the rankings.

476
00:25:19,530 --> 00:25:21,180
But you haven't even achieved that.

477
00:25:30,660 --> 00:25:31,020
She

478
00:25:32,900 --> 00:25:34,260
will sign you at a very low price

479
00:25:34,577 --> 00:25:36,300
and then make you
work for her every day.

480
00:25:36,500 --> 00:25:37,540
Ten thousand words a day.

481
00:25:38,580 --> 00:25:39,420
Not just for one day.

482
00:25:39,420 --> 00:25:40,500
Every single day.

483
00:25:41,740 --> 00:25:43,180
I've written for a whole year.

484
00:25:43,688 --> 00:25:45,380
She would think you're not good enough.

485
00:25:46,180 --> 00:25:48,940
And by not good enough,
she means you can't compare to He Han.

486
00:25:50,260 --> 00:25:51,660
You didn't write your way

487
00:25:51,780 --> 00:25:54,020
to making her a star editor
like what He Han did.

488
00:25:54,177 --> 00:25:55,777
Which of you can compare to He Han?

489
00:25:56,060 --> 00:25:57,020
She is a jerk!

490
00:25:57,620 --> 00:25:59,490
If I were you, I'd walk out right now.

491
00:25:59,490 --> 00:26:01,155
You can all think it over carefully.

492
00:26:01,660 --> 00:26:02,660
This isn't a school.

493
00:26:02,740 --> 00:26:04,060
I don't charge you tuition.

494
00:26:04,220 --> 00:26:06,300
So I have no obligation
to teach any of you.

495
00:26:07,755 --> 00:26:08,940
I expect you to be here

496
00:26:09,820 --> 00:26:11,620
to create value for me.

497
00:26:11,740 --> 00:26:12,620
Lin Zhanqiao,

498
00:26:14,060 --> 00:26:16,740
I demand compensation
for emotional distress.

499
00:26:22,180 --> 00:26:22,610
Hot water.

500
00:26:22,610 --> 00:26:22,980
Should...

501
00:26:24,580 --> 00:26:26,100
Should we go in and take a look?

502
00:26:35,900 --> 00:26:37,060
Do you know, for the company

503
00:26:37,420 --> 00:26:38,140
and me,

504
00:26:39,180 --> 00:26:40,580
what a good story means?

505
00:26:41,311 --> 00:26:43,844
And what does it mean for me
to hand it over to you?

506
00:26:44,422 --> 00:26:45,700
At the End of Yue Lu Lights

507
00:26:45,700 --> 00:26:47,100
is such a great story,

508
00:26:47,100 --> 00:26:48,688
yet you couldn't even write it well.

509
00:26:49,140 --> 00:26:50,820
All the good material you wasted

510
00:26:51,460 --> 00:26:52,500
and my time and energy,

511
00:26:53,244 --> 00:26:55,000
are you going to compensate me for that?

512
00:26:57,340 --> 00:26:58,380
Make way.

513
00:27:00,580 --> 00:27:01,540
Lin Zhanqiao,

514
00:27:02,620 --> 00:27:04,420
please, just let me keep writing.

515
00:27:04,488 --> 00:27:05,250
- Enough.
- Calm down.

516
00:27:05,260 --> 00:27:06,340
- Give me a chance.
- Enough.

517
00:27:07,380 --> 00:27:08,820
This is the office. Get back to work.

518
00:27:13,820 --> 00:27:14,340
Alright.

519
00:27:14,711 --> 00:27:15,820
You've vented your anger,

520
00:27:16,020 --> 00:27:16,940
and the damage is done.

521
00:27:17,420 --> 00:27:18,140
Calm down first.

522
00:27:20,140 --> 00:27:21,300
Come, let's talk over here.

523
00:27:25,540 --> 00:27:25,820
Come.

524
00:27:28,300 --> 00:27:29,060
Is your hand okay?

525
00:27:29,540 --> 00:27:29,980
I'm fine.

526
00:27:33,500 --> 00:27:34,600
Let me add you on WeChat.

527
00:27:35,180 --> 00:27:36,140
If anything comes up,

528
00:27:36,140 --> 00:27:37,911
I'll communicate with Ms. Lin for you.

529
00:27:38,180 --> 00:27:40,250
Recently, she's been
under a lot of pressure.

530
00:27:40,250 --> 00:27:41,533
She's too eager to deliver results,

531
00:27:41,580 --> 00:27:43,088
so she's lost her balance a bit.

532
00:27:43,980 --> 00:27:44,300
I...

533
00:27:46,740 --> 00:27:47,940
I just want a project.

534
00:27:49,500 --> 00:27:50,180
That's all.

535
00:27:51,220 --> 00:27:51,620
Got it.

536
00:27:52,488 --> 00:27:54,755
It's not just Lin Zhanqiao
who has good projects.

537
00:27:54,940 --> 00:27:56,420
I can help find one for you too.

538
00:27:57,300 --> 00:27:58,340
You're a good author.

539
00:27:58,866 --> 00:27:59,860
You won't go unnoticed.

540
00:28:01,660 --> 00:28:02,100
Thank you.

541
00:28:29,022 --> 00:28:31,022
Why did you go looking for Zhugan Dalan?

542
00:28:31,844 --> 00:28:33,300
To make sure he leaves the company

543
00:28:33,300 --> 00:28:34,866
and doesn't cause any more trouble.

544
00:28:38,940 --> 00:28:40,620
Is this for preparing

545
00:28:40,755 --> 00:28:41,666
our future company?

546
00:28:43,940 --> 00:28:45,060
As an editor,

547
00:28:45,060 --> 00:28:46,666
having more authors means more options.

548
00:29:00,140 --> 00:29:08,340
(For dramatic effect. Do not imitate.)

549
00:29:14,755 --> 00:29:16,288
What happened to your foot?

550
00:29:17,100 --> 00:29:17,933
Why are you here?

551
00:29:18,180 --> 00:29:19,177
I'm here to see you.

552
00:29:21,220 --> 00:29:21,860
Congratulations.

553
00:29:21,911 --> 00:29:23,755
Hope your collaboration
with Dai Shan goes well.

554
00:29:23,844 --> 00:29:25,530
Shattered Six States
will reach new heights.

555
00:29:25,660 --> 00:29:26,820
It is going pretty well.

556
00:29:27,140 --> 00:29:28,300
Relaxed and easy.

557
00:29:30,260 --> 00:29:31,500
I'll drive you to the hospital.

558
00:29:31,800 --> 00:29:33,400
No need. I can handle it myself.

559
00:29:33,466 --> 00:29:34,850
Where are you going? I'll come with you.

560
00:29:34,860 --> 00:29:35,980
I said I don't need your help.

561
00:29:35,980 --> 00:29:36,977
I can handle it myself.

562
00:29:37,260 --> 00:29:38,340
I promise I won't help.

563
00:29:50,300 --> 00:29:51,740
Disinfect the burn with this first,

564
00:29:51,860 --> 00:29:53,022
and then apply the ointment.

565
00:29:53,311 --> 00:29:53,911
Thank you.

566
00:29:58,155 --> 00:29:59,444
You didn't even go to the hospital,

567
00:29:59,450 --> 00:30:00,866
so how did you know
what medicine to buy?

568
00:30:01,740 --> 00:30:02,800
It's not that serious.

569
00:30:07,100 --> 00:30:08,540
I heard that your Yue Lu, whatever,

570
00:30:08,733 --> 00:30:10,088
got returned by the platform?

571
00:30:10,644 --> 00:30:12,100
And you took it out on the author?

572
00:30:15,711 --> 00:30:17,244
If a good story isn't written well,

573
00:30:17,266 --> 00:30:19,155
it's normal for
the platform to return it.

574
00:30:19,755 --> 00:30:21,355
When it was first commissioned,

575
00:30:21,740 --> 00:30:23,260
they offered a very high price.

576
00:30:24,700 --> 00:30:25,340
I know.

577
00:30:27,980 --> 00:30:28,660
How do you know?

578
00:30:28,980 --> 00:30:30,300
Of course, I know.

579
00:30:30,740 --> 00:30:32,060
They dropped your project

580
00:30:32,260 --> 00:30:34,340
and paid a lot more to buy
my Shattered Six States.

581
00:30:34,622 --> 00:30:36,280
The contract will be
signed in a few days.

582
00:30:37,533 --> 00:30:38,888
I'm doing this for your own good.

583
00:30:39,060 --> 00:30:39,911
Think about it.

584
00:30:40,380 --> 00:30:41,660
You priced it so high,

585
00:30:41,660 --> 00:30:42,888
