664
00:35:03,380 --> 00:35:04,260
The hardest part...

665
00:35:04,260 --> 00:35:05,100
(Not bad!)

666
00:35:05,100 --> 00:35:06,220
(Just got here.)

667
00:35:06,220 --> 00:35:08,350
(He Han is amazing!)
It must be finding a good editor.

668
00:35:08,380 --> 00:35:09,700
Luckily, I've already found one.

669
00:35:09,955 --> 00:35:11,044
(Congratulations!)
Dai Shan.

670
00:35:15,380 --> 00:35:16,020
Mr. He Han,

671
00:35:16,620 --> 00:35:18,100
(if you had to use one sentence)

672
00:35:18,220 --> 00:35:20,220
(to describe your collaboration
with Ms. Dai,)

673
00:35:20,340 --> 00:35:21,300
what would you say?

674
00:35:27,380 --> 00:35:29,180
A meeting that makes

675
00:35:29,340 --> 00:35:31,380
the rest of the world fade away.

676
00:35:38,422 --> 00:35:41,688
Ms. Lin, furious as if she swallowed
a bomb, is about to show up.

677
00:35:42,740 --> 00:35:43,620
Turn off the sound.

678
00:35:43,700 --> 00:35:44,333
Turn it off.

679
00:35:44,355 --> 00:35:45,088
Shut it down.

680
00:35:50,020 --> 00:35:50,780
The sound...

681
00:36:03,140 --> 00:36:04,860
We are a content-producing company,

682
00:36:05,660 --> 00:36:06,820
not an agency

683
00:36:06,820 --> 00:36:08,500
with only He Han as a signed author.

684
00:36:09,100 --> 00:36:09,660
He's gone,

685
00:36:10,220 --> 00:36:11,300
but we are fully capable

686
00:36:11,300 --> 00:36:13,500
