782
00:39:20,900 --> 00:39:22,900
A gentleman is drawn to a graceful lady.

783
00:39:29,340 --> 00:39:31,060
Although Dai Shan
doesn't quite like Mimi,

784
00:39:31,180 --> 00:39:32,540
beautiful women

785
00:39:32,660 --> 00:39:33,900
rarely get along.

786
00:39:34,220 --> 00:39:35,300
So today, you and...

787
00:39:35,700 --> 00:39:36,140
Mimi.

788
00:39:38,340 --> 00:39:39,140
What's the occasion?

789
00:39:39,540 --> 00:39:40,660
Just in a good mood.

790
00:39:40,660 --> 00:39:41,940
Came to see you, my old friend.

791
00:39:42,740 --> 00:39:44,100
Just so happens I'm busy today.

792
00:39:44,177 --> 00:39:45,733
What could you possibly be busy with?

793
00:39:45,780 --> 00:39:47,900
You don't even have
a single promising author.

794
00:39:48,660 --> 00:39:49,580
How can you say that?

795
00:39:49,820 --> 00:39:51,222
Know yourself and your enemy, right?

796
00:39:51,780 --> 00:39:52,740
He Han's name

797
00:39:52,740 --> 00:39:54,860
is a mountain they can't cross.

798
00:39:56,222 --> 00:39:57,460
The only one worth mentioning

799
00:39:58,380 --> 00:40:00,380
is the one called Ouyang Feng.

800
00:40:00,580 --> 00:40:01,300
Hong Qigong.

801
00:40:01,740 --> 00:40:02,780
Hong Qigong, sorry.

802
00:40:03,580 --> 00:40:05,300
Too bad she doesn't
plan to renew with you.

803
00:40:09,660 --> 00:40:11,900
A few years ago, I found her story

804
00:40:12,660 --> 00:40:13,900
on a second-hand site.

805
00:40:14,860 --> 00:40:16,860
I took her from a complete beginner

806
00:40:17,380 --> 00:40:19,180
all the way to a top-tier author.

807
00:40:20,500 --> 00:40:21,340
Seems like

808
00:40:21,780 --> 00:40:23,420
she's not the first

809
00:40:23,620 --> 00:40:24,940
to leave you.

810
00:40:25,260 --> 00:40:26,580
And she won't be the last.

811
00:40:33,740 --> 00:40:34,180
But

812
00:40:34,900 --> 00:40:36,020
don't feel too bad.

813
00:40:36,466 --> 00:40:39,155
Graduating from kindergarten
to primary school, changing teachers

814
00:40:39,200 --> 00:40:40,180
is perfectly normal.

815
00:40:42,260 --> 00:40:43,260
How do you know that?

816
00:40:43,777 --> 00:40:45,260
Your partner, Zhao Lanxin, told me.

817
00:40:45,620 --> 00:40:46,820
Why didn't she tell me?

818
00:40:46,911 --> 00:40:48,820
Because she and
your other partner, Ling Yikai,

819
00:40:48,900 --> 00:40:50,100
are planning to leave you

820
00:40:50,180 --> 00:40:51,555
and start something new together.

821
00:41:06,740 --> 00:41:07,220
Impossible.

822
00:41:09,780 --> 00:41:10,820
Believe it or not.

823
00:41:10,955 --> 00:41:12,660
They came to me to discuss cooperation,

824
00:41:12,660 --> 00:41:13,700
offering me shares.

825
00:41:13,900 --> 00:41:14,660
I turned them down.

826
00:41:15,180 --> 00:41:15,860
In my opinion,

827
00:41:16,340 --> 00:41:17,460
you may not be great,

828
00:41:17,620 --> 00:41:18,780
but they're even worse.

829
00:41:19,940 --> 00:41:20,300
Fine.

830
00:41:20,377 --> 00:41:21,888
If you can't handle it, come find me.

831
00:41:21,940 --> 00:41:23,244
I'll arrange a new job for you.

832
00:41:23,620 --> 00:41:23,980
Let's go.

833
00:41:24,100 --> 00:41:24,980
Thanks for the offer.

834
00:41:25,300 --> 00:41:26,820
In terms of performance

835
00:41:27,380 --> 00:41:28,060
and reputation,

836
00:41:28,660 --> 00:41:30,580
I'm among the best in the industry.

837
00:41:34,980 --> 00:41:36,500
That's because you got lucky.

838
00:41:36,900 --> 00:41:38,700
Back then, your partner was me.

839
00:41:40,060 --> 00:41:41,580
I'll find someone better than you.

840
00:41:43,300 --> 00:41:44,500
I actually quite admire

841
00:41:44,500 --> 00:41:45,980
your confidence and courage.

842
00:41:46,700 --> 00:41:48,355
Better than stupidity and ignorance.

843
00:41:50,020 --> 00:41:50,980
Alright, let's go.

844
00:41:51,620 --> 00:41:51,980
Let's go.

845
00:41:52,111 --> 00:41:53,580
The hotel across from
the company just opened.

846
00:41:53,580 --> 00:41:54,600
I'm planning to move there.

847
00:41:54,660 --> 00:41:56,460
If you need anything,
just let me know. Bye.

848
00:42:05,300 --> 00:42:06,100
Mr. He Han.

849
00:42:07,180 --> 00:42:07,900
Mr. He Han,

850
00:42:08,220 --> 00:42:09,340
I'm your fan.

851
00:42:09,460 --> 00:42:10,730
Can I get your autograph?

852
00:42:10,730 --> 00:42:11,180
Of course.

853
00:42:12,780 --> 00:42:13,220
Tell me,

854
00:42:14,500 --> 00:42:17,020
if Ling Yikai and
Zhao Lanxin go independent,

855
00:42:17,820 --> 00:42:19,020
will you go with them

856
00:42:19,460 --> 00:42:21,460
or stay here and fight it out
with Lin Zhanqiao?

857
00:42:29,540 --> 00:42:30,980
Hey, don't say that.

858
00:42:32,380 --> 00:42:35,820
If Ling Yikai and Zhao Lanxin
go independent...

859
00:42:44,180 --> 00:42:45,500
Is what He Han said true?

860
00:42:45,980 --> 00:42:46,620
Why?

861
00:42:47,260 --> 00:42:48,820
Is there a problem at work?

862
00:42:55,460 --> 00:42:56,222
Marry me.

863
00:42:57,266 --> 00:42:59,222
This is the second time
I'm proposing to you.

864
00:43:05,740 --> 00:43:07,260
And you still claim
you didn't seduce my husband?

865
00:43:07,460 --> 00:43:08,140
Not before.

866
00:43:09,060 --> 00:43:09,620
But I am now.

867
00:43:13,780 --> 00:43:14,820
No matter how great he is,

868
00:43:16,060 --> 00:43:17,020
he just doesn't like you.

869
00:43:17,420 --> 00:43:18,940
How many people actually marry for love?

870
00:43:19,460 --> 00:43:20,900
And is everyone
who marries for love happy?

871
00:43:26,460 --> 00:43:28,220
I love seeing you grit your teeth

872
00:43:28,220 --> 00:43:29,580
while losing to me.

873
00:43:30,540 --> 00:43:31,660
Remember to check my update tonight.

874
00:43:35,401 --> 00:43:36,521
(I've been thinking.)

875
00:43:37,801 --> 00:43:41,081
(Everyone's most comfortable level of intimacy)

876
00:43:41,841 --> 00:43:49,171
(is probably different.)

877
00:43:50,171 --> 00:43:51,921
♪If the sky♪

878
00:43:52,431 --> 00:43:53,831
♪And the sea♪

879
00:43:54,371 --> 00:43:56,081
♪Turned upside down♪

880
00:43:57,641 --> 00:43:59,571
♪If a swimming fish♪

881
00:43:59,971 --> 00:44:03,361
♪Fell in love with a flying bird♪

882
00:44:05,131 --> 00:44:07,101
♪If back then♪

883
00:44:07,461 --> 00:44:11,871
♪We had never let go♪

884
00:44:12,471 --> 00:44:18,751
♪We wouldn't be lost in the crowd♪

885
00:44:19,871 --> 00:44:22,021
♪We met in a thirteenth month♪

886
00:44:22,021 --> 00:44:23,891
♪Held each other in a fifth season♪

887
00:44:24,071 --> 00:44:26,511
♪And found our way back whole♪

888
00:44:27,351 --> 00:44:29,521
♪So let this surging love♪

889
00:44:29,521 --> 00:44:33,951
♪Rise like tides that never fall♪

890
00:44:34,851 --> 00:44:37,031
♪If we're caught in a pouring rain♪

891
00:44:37,031 --> 00:44:38,121
♪That's alright♪

892
00:44:38,661 --> 00:44:39,411
♪If we're buried♪

893
00:44:39,411 --> 00:44:42,111
♪By passing years all the better♪

894
00:44:42,371 --> 00:44:44,551
♪At least we still can keep♪

895
00:44:44,731 --> 00:44:49,151
♪This one eternal photograph♪

896
00:45:04,911 --> 00:45:07,201
♪We're on misaligned tracks♪

897
00:45:07,201 --> 00:45:08,961
♪Running in opposite ways♪

898
00:45:09,081 --> 00:45:11,551
♪Searching all along the way♪

899
00:45:12,351 --> 00:45:14,511
♪For the fire of our younger hearts♪

900
00:45:14,701 --> 00:45:19,611
♪And the beauty lost in time♪

901
00:45:19,611 --> 00:45:23,131
♪This time don't lose each other again♪

902
00:45:23,371 --> 00:45:24,341
♪Only after loss♪

903
00:45:24,341 --> 00:45:26,971
♪Do we learn what truly matters most♪

904
00:45:27,381 --> 00:45:29,741
♪In another time and space♪

905
00:45:29,741 --> 00:45:31,301
♪We'll stay and walk together♪

906
00:45:31,301 --> 00:45:34,131
♪Till we grow old♪

907
00:45:35,091 --> 00:45:37,381
♪But still the sky will never♪

908
00:45:37,381 --> 00:45:40,051
♪Turn with the sea♪

909
00:45:42,571 --> 00:45:44,981
♪But still a swimming fish won't♪

910
00:45:44,981 --> 00:45:50,191
♪Fall in love with a flying bird♪
